FBIS4-37751 "drnes122_a_94007" FBIS-NES-94-122 Daily Report 24 Jun 1994 ARAB AFRICA Algeria Violent Incidents Continue Throughout Country Violent Incidents Continue Throughout Country FIS: 37 Bodies Found in Mass Grave LD2406105094 Paris Radio France International in French 0630 GMT 24 Jun 94 LD2406105094 Paris Radio France International French BFN [Text] In Algeria, according to the representatives abroad of the Islamic Salvation Front [FIS], about 200 people have been killed by the security forces since the beginning of the month. According to the FIS, they include 37 young people, civilians, executed at Hama, a district in Algiers, by the security forces. Their bodies are reported to have since been found in a mass grave.
